.code-graph/

# gstack project artifacts (security reports, plans, telemetry) — local-only, may
# leak attack-path summaries onto a public repo if accidentally git-add'd.
.gstack/

# Claude Code workspace state (sessions, permission grants, local hooks) — user-specific + transient.
.claude/

# docs/ is local-only by default. Exceptions:
#  - docs/superpowers/ (design + implementation plan)
#  - docs/ADDING-NEW-HOOK.md (external contract: how to add a 6th hook)
#  - docs/RULE-HITS-SCHEMA.md (external contract: JSONL schema)
# ARCHITECTURE.md + HOOK-PROTOCOL.md are internal reference, stay local.
docs/*
!docs/superpowers/
!docs/ADDING-NEW-HOOK.md
!docs/RULE-HITS-SCHEMA.md
